1
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:19,100
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:24,432
<i>[Episode 27]</i>

3
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:38,900
<i>[Grave of Chen Nanxing]</i>

4
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:43,100
Nan Nan, Hongdou came from afar to visit you.

5
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:49,828
Please bless her with success in work and peace in life.

6
00:01:49,828 --> 00:01:53,810
She can just rest. There's no need to bless me.

7
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:58,360
I'll let you two chat. Let's go.

8
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:00,640
That's right. Don't be in a hurry.

9
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:03,380
We'll wait for you in the parking lot.

10
00:02:55,750 --> 00:03:00,350
Look. My haul.

11
00:03:01,950 --> 00:03:04,450
All those things you told me to do,

12
00:03:05,210 --> 00:03:07,662
I did most of them.

13
00:03:08,930 --> 00:03:10,946
I made friends.

14
00:03:10,946 --> 00:03:12,810
I enjoyed tons of good food.

15
00:03:12,810 --> 00:03:15,298
I had a lot of fun.

16
00:03:15,980 --> 00:03:18,900
I also rekindled the joys of being a child.

17
00:03:19,420 --> 00:03:22,930
How does that feel? It's like...

18
00:03:24,740 --> 00:03:27,148
I can't put it in words.

19
00:03:27,148 --> 00:03:30,588
It's probably the closest feeling to bliss.

20
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:40,680
I'll show you the photos.

21
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:52,400
♫ <i>Listen to the rain falling into the silent forest</i> ♫

22
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:59,354
♫ <i>Enjoy the mountainous landscape at sunset</i> ♫

23
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:07,500
♫ <i>The raindrops from the roof drip into my eyes quietly</i> ♫

24
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:14,020
♫ <i>The world is like a quiet island</i> ♫

25
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:21,880
♫ <i>The sky is turning bright without a sound</i> ♫

26
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:25,950
♫ <i>Waiting for the seabirds to call forth the ripples</i> ♫

27
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:27,350
Look. Soup with water poplar flowers.

28
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,400
Do you still remember?

29
00:04:30,410 --> 00:04:32,471
There's this one.

30
00:04:32,471 --> 00:04:37,230
♫ <i>Waiting for a ray of sunlight to shine across
the lake into my heart</i> ♫

31
00:04:37,230 --> 00:04:39,441
Do you think he's handsome?

32
00:04:39,441 --> 00:04:44,904
♫ <i>Set sail when it's windy</i> ♫

33
00:04:45,466 --> 00:04:52,169
♫ <i>The reflection of clouds, the changing moon,
and the starry sky</i> ♫

34
00:04:52,169 --> 00:04:56,020
Our agreement is always valid.

35
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,986
♫ <i>The light and shadows of the seasons</i> ♫

36
00:05:01,986 --> 00:05:07,183
♫ <i> I've seen the meteor that lights up the night sky</i> ♫

37
00:05:07,183 --> 00:05:09,580
Uncle, Aunty, I have to get going. Take care of yourselves.

38
00:05:09,580 --> 00:05:10,910
All right. Off you go.

39
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:13,680
Don't let the driver wait.

40
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:16,694
Take care on your way back.

41
00:05:16,694 --> 00:05:18,120
Text me when you're home.

42
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:21,520
Greet your parents on our behalf.

43
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:23,480
Take care.

44
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:33,380
Those are returned goods, not trash.

45
00:05:33,380 --> 00:05:34,600
They can be sold again.

46
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,770
Why are you hurling it about?

47
00:05:35,770 --> 00:05:37,280
Aren't these just tea leaves?

48
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:38,580
Should tea leaves be thrown about?

49
00:05:38,580 --> 00:05:41,561
Won't tea leaves break? Won't the tea boxes be squashed?

50
00:05:53,170 --> 00:05:54,870
What are you doing?

51
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:57,790
He merely touched you. You almost kicked him.

52
00:05:57,790 --> 00:06:00,170
If you kick someone, I need to compensate them.

53
00:06:00,170 --> 00:06:02,700
Do you know how many loans our family has?

54
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:04,880
Can I use you as mortgage?

55
00:06:06,020 --> 00:06:08,651
What? You're in a bad mood? You're throwing a hissy fit because I lectured you?

56
00:06:08,651 --> 00:06:10,860
Well, I'm in a foul mood, too.

57
00:06:11,530 --> 00:06:14,094
You aren't getting dinner tonight.

58
00:06:22,330 --> 00:06:24,980
How dare you talk back to your mom just because you came in 14th in the examinations?

59
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:28,660
If you get into Tsinghua or Peking University, is the whole family supposed to welcome you on our knees?

60
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:31,268
Watch your attitude.

61
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:34,270
Is this your good attitude?

62
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:37,100
Fine. Let's talk about this today.

63
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:40,970
Don't you know what state you're in at school?

64
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,970
<i>[Yunmiao Village Service Station]</i>
Who the heck is the real thief?

65
00:06:45,970 --> 00:06:47,940
You're the thief! You stole the land!

66
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:49,851
- You even occupied such a large plot!
- Uncle, that's enough.

67
00:06:49,851 --> 00:06:50,500
Measure it.

68
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,580
- Wait, Uncle.
- Do it!

69
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:54,250
- Let Xiao Huang measure the land.
- Can we calm down?

70
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:56,070
Let's see if the ridging affected your fields.

71
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:57,730
Give me back my corn! Don't fight!

72
00:06:57,730 --> 00:06:59,860
Give me back my corn!

73
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:01,630
Stop it!

74
00:07:02,410 --> 00:07:06,510
Uncles, we can't just talk it out now, can we?

75
00:07:07,700 --> 00:07:10,450
Come on. Smash it on me.

76
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:13,280
Look what you did to me last time. It hasn't even healed yet.

77
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:16,760
Smash me. Vent all your anger.

78
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:21,490
Don't start fights all year round when sowing seeds and harvesting.

79
00:07:21,490 --> 00:07:23,064
I'm sick and tired.

80
00:07:23,064 --> 00:07:25,660
Beat me, right here. Come on. Use this. Whack me with it.

81
00:07:25,660 --> 00:07:28,190
Here, hit me.

82
00:07:28,190 --> 00:07:31,021
A'Yao, please don't be like that.

83
00:08:10,210 --> 00:08:11,850
Why hasn't she arrived?

84
00:08:11,850 --> 00:08:13,400
Isn't she already in a taxi?

85
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:16,080
Yes. How's your sauce?

86
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:18,660
It's ready. The fat has been stewed.

87
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:20,930
That's great.

88
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:24,190
How about I pick her up at the entrance of the estate?

89
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:27,270
You should hurry over. You can't sit still at home anyway.

90
00:08:27,270 --> 00:08:29,920
It's like there's a nail under your butt.

91
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:33,900
She's back! Cook the noodles!

92
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:36,380
Dou'er, you're back.

93
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:37,390
Dad!

94
00:08:37,390 --> 00:08:38,980
The apron is dirty.

95
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:40,570
What are you stewing? Smells great!

96
00:08:40,570 --> 00:08:42,140
My turn!

97
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:43,940
I bet you had too much fun and didn't want to come back.

98
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:45,450
Your waist got thicker.

99
00:08:45,450 --> 00:08:47,440
Get lost. Wash your hands!

100
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,380
- Where are the belongings I sent back?
- They're in your room.

101
00:08:49,380 --> 00:08:51,050
- Hurry up.
- Okay.

102
00:08:51,050 --> 00:08:52,636
Come on!

103
00:08:52,636 --> 00:08:56,730
Your mom made your favorite noodles with fried bean sauce.

104
00:08:56,730 --> 00:08:59,680
I'll cook the noodles!

105
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:07,000
Here you go. The sweet garlic you asked for.

106
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,650
Why haven't you two eaten yet?

107
00:09:08,650 --> 00:09:11,746
Your dad insisted on waiting for you.

108
00:09:11,746 --> 00:09:13,650
Dumplings for leaving, noodles for coming back.

109
00:09:13,650 --> 00:09:16,260
Your mom was worried that you ate on the way back.

110
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:18,670
Here you go. Eat up before it gets cold.

111
00:09:18,670 --> 00:09:21,850
Here's the thing. I knew you guys would make me a delicious meal,

112
00:09:21,850 --> 00:09:23,340
so I kept my stomach empty.

113
00:09:23,340 --> 00:09:25,700
That's a smart girl.

114
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:28,120
How is it? Is it salty?

115
00:09:29,290 --> 00:09:33,020
Tastes amazing. Number one in the world.

116
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:37,896
How are Nan Nan's parents?

117
00:09:38,930 --> 00:09:41,070
They're doing all right.

118
00:09:41,070 --> 00:09:45,000
Well, they asked me to say hello to you.

119
00:09:48,530 --> 00:09:52,882
Don't sigh. How's the new home coming along?

120
00:09:52,882 --> 00:09:54,100
We're almost done.

121
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:56,650
The place has been cleaned and tested for formaldehyde.

122
00:09:56,650 --> 00:09:57,870
The air quality has met the standards.

123
00:09:57,870 --> 00:10:02,400
Lately, your mom and I have moved many things over.

124
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:05,650
We just don't know what to do with the junk in your room.

125
00:10:05,650 --> 00:10:06,920
Do we throw or keep them?

126
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:08,630
We left them for you to pack.

127
00:10:08,630 --> 00:10:10,690
I don't keep junk.

128
00:10:10,690 --> 00:10:12,530
Take a look for yourself.

129
00:10:12,530 --> 00:10:16,110
You still have magazines from 20 years ago. Why are you keeping them?

130
00:10:16,110 --> 00:10:17,992
As a keepsake.

131
00:10:17,992 --> 00:10:21,930
I think you can live with Grandma Liu from the next building.

132
00:10:21,930 --> 00:10:23,734
She keeps everything.

133
00:10:23,734 --> 00:10:25,690
She brings junk home every day.

134
00:10:25,690 --> 00:10:27,930
She never listens to her son or daughter-in-law.

135
00:10:27,930 --> 00:10:31,682
Her home has so much junk that there's no space to walk.

136
00:10:31,682 --> 00:10:34,874
Your mom just loves to exaggerate.

137
00:10:34,874 --> 00:10:38,850
I don't think there's much stuff. Just one cabinet. It's not too much.

138
00:10:38,850 --> 00:10:40,290
Weren't you the one who said this the other day?

139
00:10:40,290 --> 00:10:43,958
“Should we dump Dou's cabinet of junk?"

140
00:10:43,958 --> 00:10:45,740
Now, you're playing the good guy.

141
00:10:45,740 --> 00:10:49,280
When have I called that junk? I said they were old items.

142
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:52,610
Junk. Items. You didn't hear clearly.

143
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:54,670
Fine, I'll record your speech next time.

144
00:10:54,670 --> 00:10:56,630
I didn't say that anyway.

145
00:10:56,630 --> 00:10:58,260
This is selective memory loss.

146
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,550
He only remembers what he wants,

147
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:02,491
and erases everything that he doesn't want to recall.

148
00:12:08,810 --> 00:12:10,960
<i>Second Sister, Aunty said you're back.</i>

149
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:13,020
<i>My mom and I will go to your house soon.</i>

150
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:16,464
<i>Remember to buy me cherries in advance.</i>

151
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:21,959
<i>[Xie Zhiyao: Have you met her parents?]
[Xu Hongdou: Nope, I just landed. I need to take a bus.]</i>

152
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:24,792
<i>[Xie Zhiyao: Take care.]
[Xu Hongdou: Okay!]</i>

153
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:32,520
<i>[What are you doing...]</i>

154
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:01,368
<i>[Moments]
[Dou: My mom's handmade noodles are the best in the universe.]</i>

155
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:09,872
<i>[Mai: I'll lick the bowl clean after you're done eating.]</i>

156
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:19,752
<i>[Reply to Mai: You're really a spider, always on the web...]</i>

157
00:13:27,150 --> 00:13:31,350
Yang Zhinan is way out of line!

158
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:33,790
We just started dating, and it was his first birthday.

159
00:13:33,790 --> 00:13:36,030
I even made a point of asking him the date.

160
00:13:36,030 --> 00:13:40,000
Isn't it obvious that I wanted to buy him a gift and celebrate together?

161
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,120
At five o'clock today, I went to pick up the cake.

162
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:46,012
I even got my hair styled for him.

163
00:13:46,012 --> 00:13:48,150
I called him to see if he had gotten off work.

164
00:13:48,150 --> 00:13:50,630
He told me he didn't have work today.

165
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:53,778
He asked for leave and went home.

166
00:13:53,778 --> 00:13:56,482
He went home?

167
00:13:56,482 --> 00:13:58,830
I asked him why he had gone home.

168
00:13:58,830 --> 00:14:01,360
He said he took time off to go home for his birthday.

169
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:02,750
He said it was okay.

170
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:06,350
I can give him the birthday gift tomorrow.

171
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,650
I'm so pissed off. I want to break up with him!

172
00:14:10,650 --> 00:14:12,944
You don't have to be so extreme, Xiao Qin.

173
00:14:12,944 --> 00:14:15,790
That kid might not have dated anyone before.

174
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:18,410
So, he's a simple guy. He doesn't know about such things.

175
00:14:18,410 --> 00:14:21,360
How can he be clueless? Doesn't he want to be with me every day?

176
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:23,750
Won't you get bored if you're together every day?

177
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:25,950
He'll get bored of me?

178
00:14:25,950 --> 00:14:27,960
How can he get bored of me?

179
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:30,140
I wasn't talking about him.

180
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:34,140
I mean... you guys shouldn't be joined at the hip.

181
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:36,580
People get tired no matter how beautiful you are.

182
00:14:36,580 --> 00:14:39,948
When you're in love, you need to give your partner space.

183
00:14:39,948 --> 00:14:41,300
Space?

184
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:43,320
Why does love need space?

185
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,270
Haven't I given him enough space?

186
00:14:45,270 --> 00:14:48,270
I didn't even ask him to call me during work.

187
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:51,310
He just needs to send me his location every 30 minutes.

188
00:14:52,270 --> 00:14:55,460
Xiao Qin, I don't mean to lecture you.

189
00:14:55,460 --> 00:14:58,080
Yang Guanjun, watch your mouth.

190
00:14:58,080 --> 00:15:01,240
In terms of seniority, I‘m your sister-in-law.

191
00:15:04,870 --> 00:15:06,910
Jiabao and Guobao call you their sister.

192
00:15:06,910 --> 00:15:08,320
Am I supposed to call you sister-in-law?

193
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:11,630
If you agree with me, I'll call you Brother Guanjun.

194
00:15:11,630 --> 00:15:15,594
If you disagree with me, I'll drag out our seniority gap.

195
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,670
I'm not opposing your views.

196
00:15:18,670 --> 00:15:21,178
I'm just offering advice as someone who's been there.

197
00:15:21,178 --> 00:15:25,600
If you guys hang out all the time, you'll get sick of each other quickly. Got it?

198
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:28,110
He'll get sick of me?

199
00:15:28,110 --> 00:15:30,358
How can he?

200
00:15:30,358 --> 00:15:32,570
My goodness! Uncle A'Yao, did you hear him?

201
00:15:32,570 --> 00:15:35,601
- Yes, I did.
- How can he get sick of me? What's wrong with him?

202
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:37,386
That's outrageous!

203
00:15:37,386 --> 00:15:39,612
Yang Zhinan is preposterous!

204
00:15:39,612 --> 00:15:40,790
What space does he even need?

205
00:15:40,790 --> 00:15:42,850
What space does love need?

206
00:15:42,850 --> 00:15:46,380
Shouldn't you spend every second with your partner? Right?

207
00:15:46,380 --> 00:15:48,670
Xiao Qin looks so gorgeous today.

208
00:15:48,670 --> 00:15:52,490
She even bought a cake, but Yang Zhinan went home!

209
00:15:52,490 --> 00:15:55,790
If a guy has a girlfriend, isn't he supposed to spend his birthday with her?

210
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:57,370
Do you know what this means?

211
00:15:57,370 --> 00:15:58,950
What does this mean?

212
00:15:58,950 --> 00:16:01,310
It means that he doesn't care much about you.

213
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:07,944
Yang Zhinan is a jerk!

214
00:16:07,944 --> 00:16:09,550
I want to break up with him!

215
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:12,960
Break up! Right now! Call him! Tell him you want to break up.

216
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,070
- Outrageous!
- Xiao Qin, don't call him.

217
00:16:15,070 --> 00:16:16,480
Yang Guanjun, you stay right there.

218
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:19,080
You're not going to change my mind.

219
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:26,420
Yang Zhinan, I gave you space. Let's break up!

220
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:36,448
I no longer have a boyfriend.

221
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:40,700
Xiao Qin, listen to my advice.

222
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:43,878
Let's not shed tears for love.

223
00:16:47,030 --> 00:16:50,350
We have to focus on our careers. Got it?

224
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:55,204
I don't even have a career.

225
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:02,020
Xie Zhiyao, why did you fan the flames?

226
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:04,440
In the blink of an eye, Xiao Qin is single again.

227
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:06,550
Since you refuse to support her today,

228
00:17:06,550 --> 00:17:09,150
I'll hold this against you.

229
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:17,768
You're just jealous that she's dating someone while you're single. Right?

230
00:17:17,768 --> 00:17:20,790
Yang Guanjun, don't you dare speak to Uncle A'Yao like that.

231
00:17:20,790 --> 00:17:22,920
Uncle A'Yao is my only ally in this world.

232
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:26,430
Yes. I'll always support you.

233
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:31,540
Uncle A'Yao, why don't you marry me?

234
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:39,770
Fabulous, you dug your own grave.

235
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:47,270
What's wrong? Is it the fishbone?

236
00:17:47,270 --> 00:17:48,400
Karma is real.

237
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,000
Uncle A'Yao.

238
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,050
Are you really choking?

239
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:56,371
Don't eat the cake! Go to the hospital! Let's go.

240
00:17:56,371 --> 00:17:59,240
Uncle A'Yao, don't cough. You're scaring me.

241
00:18:05,110 --> 00:18:08,270
Don't swallow your saliva. Hang in there.

242
00:18:08,270 --> 00:18:11,840
Fortunately, it's not very deep. It's just stuck in your tonsils.

243
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:14,662
Your tonsils look gorgeous.

244
00:18:15,350 --> 00:18:17,606
Very good.

245
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:20,384
It's out.

246
00:18:20,384 --> 00:18:22,960
It's been a long time since I saw someone swallow such a huge fishbone.

247
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:25,060
How did that happen?

248
00:18:25,060 --> 00:18:26,170
I didn't notice it.

249
00:18:26,170 --> 00:18:28,780
Tons of people need emergency care daily because of fishbones.

250
00:18:28,780 --> 00:18:30,490
You must be careful while eating fish.

251
00:18:30,490 --> 00:18:33,190
You're pretty smart and came to the hospital.

252
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:36,370
Many people drink vinegar and swallow rice, driving the fishbone deeper.

253
00:18:36,370 --> 00:18:38,950
It'll be dangerous if your esophagus gets cut.

254
00:18:40,930 --> 00:18:44,130
Just a moment. Let me take a picture.

255
00:18:44,130 --> 00:18:46,550
Didn't your girlfriend come with you?

256
00:18:46,550 --> 00:18:49,590
You accompanied that pretty lady for her IV drip, right?

257
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,060
Thank goodness you're fine.

258
00:18:56,060 --> 00:18:58,340
- You scared the hell out of me.
- Let's go.

259
00:18:58,340 --> 00:19:00,900
Xiao Qin, I choked on a fishbone once as a child.

260
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:02,640
It was bigger than this one.

261
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:03,750
This big.

262
00:19:03,750 --> 00:19:05,110
That big?

263
00:19:05,110 --> 00:19:07,030
At that time, I was scared to death.

264
00:19:07,030 --> 00:19:10,070
You must be careful when eating fish.

265
00:19:10,070 --> 00:19:11,690
You even let him eat the cake.

266
00:19:11,690 --> 00:19:13,640
The doctor already said to avoid food.

267
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:14,980
I didn't know he couldn't even eat cake.

268
00:19:14,980 --> 00:19:19,400
<i>[Moments]
[Xie Zhiyao: A huge fish bone was stuck in my tonsils]
Now you know.</i>

269
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:26,500
♫ <i>I've been alone into the unknown</i> ♫

270
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:33,650
♫ <i>Could navigate through the dark</i> ♫

271
00:19:33,650 --> 00:19:40,360
♫ <i>I'm searching for a meadow of mine</i> ♫

272
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:47,250
♫ <i>Till you came in with the breeze</i> ♫

273
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:50,180
♫ <i>A feeling rushes over me</i> ♫

274
00:19:50,180 --> 00:19:54,780
♫ <i>Spills my heart into the field</i> ♫

275
00:19:54,780 --> 00:20:01,480
♫ <i>I know it, I will be yours</i> ♫

276
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:04,680
♫ <i>Would you ask for any horse</i> ♫

277
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:09,170
♫ <i>But this one inside your heart</i> ♫

278
00:20:09,170 --> 00:20:12,186
She didn't even give me a like.

279
00:20:12,186 --> 00:20:14,800
I even accompanied you for the IV drips.

280
00:20:26,910 --> 00:20:29,730
A fish bone stuck in his throat?

281
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:33,390
<i>[11 hours ago]
[Likes: Nana, Ye Sen, Ma Qiushan, Mai, A'Yuan...]
[Mai: As expected of my idol!]</i>

282
00:20:33,390 --> 00:20:37,720
♫ <i>Spills my heart into the field</i> ♫

283
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:44,480
♫ <i>I know it, I will be yours</i> ♫

284
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:47,580
♫ <i>Would you ask for any horse</i> ♫

285
00:20:48,350 --> 00:20:50,554
<i>Dou, wake up for breakfast.</i>

286
00:20:50,554 --> 00:20:52,110
Okay.

287
00:20:52,110 --> 00:20:53,881
<i>Hurry up.</i>

288
00:20:53,881 --> 00:20:59,200
<i>[How did you get that stuck...]</i>

289
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:06,400
♫ <i>You ask me if the wind could sing</i> ♫

290
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:09,326
♫ <i>We close our eyes to feel</i> ♫

291
00:21:09,326 --> 00:21:11,226
Do you have a headache?

292
00:21:13,510 --> 00:21:18,382
Eat properly, or you won't have energy.

293
00:21:18,382 --> 00:21:22,299
People need energy even to feel sad.

294
00:21:22,299 --> 00:21:26,400
Why do you think I'm sad? Goodness, Granny.

295
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:30,980
I'll eat it later.

296
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:36,380
Granny, she doesn't send me messages.

297
00:21:36,380 --> 00:21:39,020
I can't really take the initiative either.

298
00:21:39,020 --> 00:21:42,040
Why can't you send her a message first?

299
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:44,490
Is the signal bad with your phone?

300
00:21:44,490 --> 00:21:46,790
I'm being serious here.

301
00:21:46,790 --> 00:21:49,581
Here's the thing. I'm not in the position to initiate anything.

302
00:21:49,581 --> 00:21:53,250
Before she left, I already told her.

303
00:21:54,010 --> 00:21:56,030
What did you say?

304
00:21:58,780 --> 00:22:02,880
I told her... I liked her.

305
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:11,490
I'll stop talking if that's your reaction.

306
00:22:11,490 --> 00:22:16,894
Keep going. You like her, and?

307
00:22:16,894 --> 00:22:20,760
Nothing else. I confessed my feelings and that's it.

308
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:24,980
Well, did she ask to sever all contact?

309
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:27,740
Of course not. She just said to keep in touch.

310
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:29,960
We're still friends and all that.

311
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,410
Isn't that telling?

312
00:22:31,410 --> 00:22:35,819
You've spoken your mind, and now you're shy.

313
00:22:35,819 --> 00:22:38,840
Be bolder. Take the initiative.

314
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:44,986
An online relationship might just unfold.

315
00:22:44,986 --> 00:22:49,110
Granny, she doesn't want an online relationship or a long-distance one.

316
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:51,100
In that case, put in some effort.

317
00:22:51,100 --> 00:22:54,410
Fly from Yunnan to Beijing, and then from Beijing to Yunnan.

318
00:22:54,410 --> 00:22:58,650
I have money. I saved money for you.

319
00:22:58,650 --> 00:23:02,390
You saved money for me? How much have you saved?

320
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:04,350
Wait a minute.

321
00:23:11,060 --> 00:23:12,660
Look.

322
00:23:23,650 --> 00:23:25,350
What...

323
00:23:32,300 --> 00:23:36,052
I was going to give you this money

324
00:23:36,052 --> 00:23:39,900
if your business didn't work out here.

325
00:23:39,900 --> 00:23:42,020
You can go back to Beijing.

326
00:23:42,020 --> 00:23:47,546
If you get married, these will be the funds for your family.

327
00:23:47,546 --> 00:23:51,210
Of course, it isn't enough to buy a house or land.

328
00:23:51,210 --> 00:23:55,134
But it's enough as emergency funds.

329
00:23:57,580 --> 00:24:03,880
I think Hongdou's departure was good for both of you.

330
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:08,332
Youngsters like you guys fall in and out of love quickly.

331
00:24:08,332 --> 00:24:10,650
Once she left, you had time to cool your head.

332
00:24:10,650 --> 00:24:14,060
If you still miss each other,

333
00:24:14,060 --> 00:24:18,508
then start considering how to move forward.

334
00:24:18,508 --> 00:24:21,386
Don't be in a hurry.

335
00:24:24,730 --> 00:24:29,954
Your grandpa and I started with nothing.

336
00:24:29,954 --> 00:24:32,930
We spent a lifetime understanding a truth.

337
00:24:32,930 --> 00:24:37,610
That is to fight for what you desire.

338
00:24:37,610 --> 00:24:40,510
Don't wait for someone else's offerings.

339
00:24:43,010 --> 00:24:46,440
Cheer up. Don't be so downcast.

340
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:48,210
Got it?

341
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:51,900
If you do, then eat up.

342
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:56,406
Granny, isn't the bankbook for me?

343
00:24:56,406 --> 00:24:59,630
You can have it when you buy a ticket.

344
00:25:00,650 --> 00:25:02,354
But I'm still curious.

345
00:25:02,354 --> 00:25:05,170
How did you save up so much money?

346
00:25:06,930 --> 00:25:11,059
I just called your dad all the time

347
00:25:11,059 --> 00:25:14,650
complaining about my headaches or sore butt.

348
00:25:14,650 --> 00:25:18,460
I asked him for money and saved it for you.

349
00:25:19,450 --> 00:25:22,990
Let me answer this call. It's from Xiao Huang.

350
00:25:22,990 --> 00:25:24,110
Xiao Huang, what is it?

351
00:25:24,110 --> 00:25:25,200
<i>Hello, Old Xie?</i>

352
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:27,780
<i>Shaohua Bookstore's team will arrive in five days.</i>

353
00:25:27,780 --> 00:25:29,940
- It's been confirmed?
<i>- Yes, it's confirmed. Come over for a meeting.</i>

354
00:25:29,940 --> 00:25:32,000
Okay, I'll be right over.

355
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,280
Granny, I have to attend a meeting at the village committee.

356
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:36,340
You're missing another meal.

357
00:25:36,340 --> 00:25:38,340
- Take this with you and eat it on the way.
- Okay.

358
00:25:38,340 --> 00:25:39,680
Can I have that one?

359
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:42,180
Thank you, Granny.

360
00:25:42,180 --> 00:25:43,850
I'm off.

361
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:56,650
When I was in Yunmiao Village,

362
00:25:56,650 --> 00:25:58,830
I got up before dawn and went to the town

363
00:25:58,830 --> 00:26:01,960
to eat small pot rice noodles at the market.

364
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:04,380
Can a sloth like you wake up early?

365
00:26:04,380 --> 00:26:05,860
I had someone to wake me up.

366
00:26:05,860 --> 00:26:09,780
Xie Zhiyao's home is an alley away from the courtyard I lived in.

367
00:26:09,780 --> 00:26:12,100
I can see their yard from my window.

368
00:26:12,100 --> 00:26:13,300
He's an early riser.

369
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:15,590
So, he'll hurl pebbles at my window.

370
00:26:15,590 --> 00:26:19,801
You know what? Only locals would know about such a shop.

371
00:26:23,970 --> 00:26:25,830
Is that the young man

372
00:26:25,830 --> 00:26:27,920
who went home to start a business?

373
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:30,140
That's him. He's very nice.

374
00:26:33,060 --> 00:26:35,308
How old is he?

375
00:26:35,308 --> 00:26:37,300
In his early 30s.

376
00:26:39,410 --> 00:26:41,900
He seems like quite a good catch.

377
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:43,940
Why is he still single?

378
00:26:43,940 --> 00:26:45,780
He hasn't met the right girl.

379
00:26:45,780 --> 00:26:49,620
He said his last relationship was when he was still in college.

380
00:26:49,620 --> 00:26:52,230
That's over a decade ago.

381
00:26:53,860 --> 00:26:57,612
Is he single because he has issues with...

382
00:26:57,612 --> 00:26:59,566
Mom!

383
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:02,300
What's embarrassing about that?

384
00:27:02,300 --> 00:27:04,680
He just hasn't met the right person.

385
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:07,748
No one would think about physical deficiencies.

386
00:27:07,748 --> 00:27:11,490
Everyone is bound to think this way. What else could it be?

387
00:27:11,490 --> 00:27:12,690
He set the bar too high.

388
00:27:12,690 --> 00:27:14,060
Your daughter doesn't have a boyfriend either.

389
00:27:14,060 --> 00:27:15,300
Is there something wrong with me, too?

390
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:17,010
There's definitely no problem with you.

391
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:19,100
It's normal for girls to marry late these days.

392
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:20,830
Mom, you have double standards.

393
00:27:20,830 --> 00:27:26,290
Of course. I'd definitely praise my own child.

394
00:27:26,290 --> 00:27:29,060
You're just too far away from each other.

395
00:27:31,140 --> 00:27:34,670
Eat up. I'll take you out after breakfast.

396
00:27:34,670 --> 00:27:36,410
I'm not going fishing with Dad.

397
00:27:36,410 --> 00:27:37,930
No one mentioned fishing.

398
00:27:37,930 --> 00:27:40,110
Let's go pick peaches, okay?

399
00:27:40,110 --> 00:27:41,140
Okay, peach picking.

400
00:27:41,140 --> 00:27:42,840
Eat up.

401
00:27:50,930 --> 00:27:55,070
The peaches Hongdou picked are excellent.

402
00:27:55,070 --> 00:27:57,570
Each of them is at least half a catty, right?

403
00:27:57,570 --> 00:28:00,042
It's so sweet.

404
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:02,080
What did she say?

405
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:05,130
Hope to hear good news from you.
<i>[The peaches are very sweet. I wanted to let you guys try them.]</i>

406
00:28:05,130 --> 00:28:06,770
[Has the wind risen over there? Hope to hear good news from you.- Xu Hongdou.]
- What good news?

407
00:28:06,770 --> 00:28:08,950
She's talking about the bookstore.

408
00:28:10,780 --> 00:28:12,720
Granny, look here.

409
00:28:14,100 --> 00:28:16,550
This one is particularly great.

410
00:28:16,550 --> 00:28:18,590
Let me have a look.

411
00:28:19,550 --> 00:28:21,530
You took such an ugly picture of me! So ugly!

412
00:28:21,530 --> 00:28:22,910
You're cute. You don't get it.

413
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:24,110
What? Cute?

414
00:28:24,110 --> 00:28:26,810
I already sent it. I sent it over.

415
00:28:27,350 --> 00:28:29,530
I'll beat you to a pulp.

416
00:28:29,530 --> 00:28:32,230
Stop. I'll take a box to Granny Huailan.

417
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,031
Ouch!

418
00:28:33,031 --> 00:28:34,566
I'm off!

419
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:40,300
Here, have some peaches.

420
00:28:45,170 --> 00:28:47,270
It's sweet. Really sweet.

421
00:28:47,270 --> 00:28:49,210
She sent over 200 catties over.

422
00:28:49,210 --> 00:28:51,790
How much does the express delivery cost?

423
00:28:52,550 --> 00:28:53,580
What a pity.

424
00:28:53,580 --> 00:28:56,730
She's a good lady, but she just can't get used to living here.

425
00:28:56,730 --> 00:28:58,300
Did you see A'Yao the other day?

426
00:28:58,300 --> 00:29:00,950
He was fuming, and then he fell silent.

427
00:29:00,950 --> 00:29:04,450
He's like a deflated balloon, utterly listless.

428
00:29:04,450 --> 00:29:06,240
Didn't he drop by this morning?

429
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:07,540
He seemed pretty cheery.

430
00:29:07,540 --> 00:29:10,780
He was in good spirits and smiling from ear to ear.

431
00:29:11,650 --> 00:29:15,100
Men and women are different.

432
00:29:15,100 --> 00:29:17,860
If a man breaks up, he won't be heartbroken for more than a week.

433
00:29:17,860 --> 00:29:19,720
Even Chairman Xie is no exception.

434
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:22,634
I'm disappointed in all men.

435
00:29:22,634 --> 00:29:24,990
You've hit the nail on the head. Men forget easily.

436
00:29:24,990 --> 00:29:26,300
Look at Baoping.

437
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:29,900
She didn't remarry even though it's been years since her husband passed away.

438
00:29:29,900 --> 00:29:31,841
- Exactly.
- What about the old crow in the village?

439
00:29:31,841 --> 00:29:34,780
Less than 100 days had passed since his wife's death,

440
00:29:34,780 --> 00:29:37,310
but he already went to a matchmaker for a new wife.

441
00:29:37,310 --> 00:29:38,250
Shameless!

442
00:29:38,250 --> 00:29:40,010
That old man is shameless.

443
00:29:40,010 --> 00:29:41,710
Shameless.

444
00:29:42,210 --> 00:29:45,250
Chuchu and Xiaoyue, don't despair.

445
00:29:45,250 --> 00:29:47,060
There are still good men around,

446
00:29:47,060 --> 00:29:49,772
like Guanjun.

447
00:29:50,550 --> 00:29:52,982
Guanjun is really a good lad.

448
00:29:52,982 --> 00:29:54,900
Don't blow your own horn like A'Gui.

449
00:29:54,900 --> 00:29:57,300
You'll regret when problems arise.

450
00:29:57,300 --> 00:29:58,800
You're right.

451
00:29:58,800 --> 00:29:59,650
Is it sweet?

452
00:29:59,650 --> 00:30:01,650
It is.

453
00:30:08,970 --> 00:30:10,570
Open your mouth.

454
00:30:12,750 --> 00:30:14,550
Is it sweet?

455
00:30:14,550 --> 00:30:16,180
Yeah.

456
00:30:16,970 --> 00:30:18,170
Don't stare at me.

457
00:30:18,170 --> 00:30:20,338
Try one.

458
00:30:25,140 --> 00:30:26,640
It's sweet.

459
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:32,650
Sister, why did you ask Na Na for those wine bottles, cans, and jars?

460
00:30:32,650 --> 00:30:34,920
I want to do magic.

461
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:36,950
Don't leave me hanging.

462
00:30:37,450 --> 00:30:39,730
Don't throw away the peach pits when you're done eating.

463
00:30:39,730 --> 00:30:41,430
Keep them for me.

464
00:30:41,430 --> 00:30:43,450
What do you need them for?

465
00:30:43,450 --> 00:30:47,110
These contain life. Got it?

466
00:30:49,900 --> 00:30:52,000
Come here.

467
00:30:52,540 --> 00:30:55,140
Your hair is too long.

468
00:30:55,140 --> 00:30:57,000
I'll cut it for you.

469
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:58,450
You can cut hair?

470
00:30:58,450 --> 00:31:00,611
Of course. I cut my daughter's hair.

471
00:31:00,611 --> 00:31:01,930
That's great.

472
00:31:01,930 --> 00:31:04,301
You know what? The barbershop here is too expensive.

473
00:31:04,301 --> 00:31:06,340
It costs several dozen yuan for a haircut.

474
00:31:06,340 --> 00:31:08,690
In return, you have to sing a song for me.

475
00:31:08,690 --> 00:31:10,950
Deal. What song do you want to hear?

476
00:31:10,950 --> 00:31:12,060
"Wind."

477
00:31:12,060 --> 00:31:16,080
♪ Blow on. Blowing on our faces... ♪

478
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:18,236
I'll get my guitar.

479
00:31:20,010 --> 00:31:22,010
Jiahui!

480
00:31:37,890 --> 00:31:42,201
Hello. This is our special sugared peach.

481
00:31:42,201 --> 00:31:43,710
Please have a taste.

482
00:31:43,710 --> 00:31:45,320
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

483
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,131
You're welcome.

484
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:53,080
♫ <i>A breeze wafts through some parts of the world</i> ♫

485
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:54,540
Hello.

486
00:31:54,540 --> 00:31:58,460
This is our special sugared peach. Please try it.

487
00:31:58,460 --> 00:32:00,960
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

488
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:03,010
Please enjoy.

489
00:32:04,950 --> 00:32:08,780
You guys look so stiff. It looks too intentional. Come on, look at each other.

490
00:32:08,780 --> 00:32:11,950
Looking at each other. You have to smile gently,

491
00:32:11,950 --> 00:32:14,300
like this peach is delicious.

492
00:32:14,300 --> 00:32:18,200
Okay, that's it. Three, two, one.

493
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:21,450
Nice. Off you go.

494
00:32:21,450 --> 00:32:24,300
♫ <i>Although the seasons go by</i> ♫

495
00:32:24,300 --> 00:32:27,180
Why do I feel we've been used like tools?

496
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:28,618
So be it.

497
00:32:28,618 --> 00:32:33,658
I'm worried that he'll dash to Beijing just for Xu Hongdou.

498
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:39,000
I've lost my appetite.

499
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:42,800
♫ <i>Maybe things will go your way ♫</i>

500
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:47,808
♫ <i>Sometimes I need a beautiful smile</i> ♫

501
00:32:47,808 --> 00:32:52,310
♫ <i>Although the seasons go by</i> ♫

502
00:32:52,310 --> 00:32:56,000
♫ <i>I'll still love passionately like a youth</i> ♫

503
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,650
