504
00:32:57,650 --> 00:33:00,980
Let's take a look at the gifts your aunty prepared for you.

505
00:33:00,980 --> 00:33:05,488
♫ <i>Make a little wish and pray</i> ♫

506
00:33:05,488 --> 00:33:07,100
♫ <i>Maybe things will go your way ♫</i>

507
00:33:07,100 --> 00:33:09,700
Tiger-head shoes?

508
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:12,110
These were made by a granny in Yunnan.

509
00:33:12,110 --> 00:33:13,300
She refused to accept payment.

510
00:33:13,300 --> 00:33:16,420
She put her heart into every stitch.

511
00:33:18,250 --> 00:33:20,910
If Grandma was still alive,

512
00:33:20,910 --> 00:33:23,210
she would've made tiger-head shoes for my baby, too.

513
00:33:23,210 --> 00:33:26,950
Granny smells just like our grandma. Smell it.

514
00:33:29,170 --> 00:33:31,170
It's true.

515
00:33:32,730 --> 00:33:35,010
It's the smell of boiled peanuts.

516
00:33:35,010 --> 00:33:37,144
Not the smell of baking bread?

517
00:33:37,144 --> 00:33:39,518
It's boiled peanuts.

518
00:33:44,930 --> 00:33:46,530
Wipe your tears quickly.

519
00:33:46,530 --> 00:33:50,489
If Mom comes by, she'll think I did something to you.

520
00:33:50,489 --> 00:33:52,410
I'm fine. I'm just pregnant.

521
00:33:52,410 --> 00:33:55,094
So, I'm unusually emotional.

522
00:33:58,930 --> 00:34:02,730
Kexin, how is your husband treating you?

523
00:34:02,730 --> 00:34:04,344
Not bad.

524
00:34:04,344 --> 00:34:06,090
We're both quite lazy.

525
00:34:06,090 --> 00:34:07,780
His mother spoiled him until he knows nothing.

526
00:34:07,780 --> 00:34:09,820
My mom spoiled me until I know nothing.

527
00:34:09,820 --> 00:34:13,000
We're two grown babies. We can't frown upon each other.

528
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,422
Fortune favors fools.

529
00:34:16,422 --> 00:34:19,050
Second Sister, I picked up a piece of trash.

530
00:34:19,050 --> 00:34:22,250
You have to be careful and find a good partner.

531
00:34:24,450 --> 00:34:26,330
How good does he have to be?

532
00:34:27,090 --> 00:34:28,740
Firstly, he has to be handsome.

533
00:34:28,740 --> 00:34:29,930
He needs to earn good money.

534
00:34:29,930 --> 00:34:32,060
What else? He must have a nice family.

535
00:34:32,060 --> 00:34:34,110
His parents have to be reasonable.

536
00:34:34,110 --> 00:34:35,740
He has to be able to afford a house in Beijing.

537
00:34:35,740 --> 00:34:38,860
At the very least, he should hold a Beijing household registration.

538
00:34:38,860 --> 00:34:40,340
What if he's not from Beijing?

539
00:34:40,340 --> 00:34:42,700
Shanghai is fine, too.

540
00:34:43,700 --> 00:34:45,050
What about Yunnan?

541
00:34:45,050 --> 00:34:46,550
Yunnan?

542
00:34:46,550 --> 00:34:48,658
Yunnan is...

543
00:34:49,530 --> 00:34:52,050
Did you fall in love with someone from Yunnan?

544
00:34:52,050 --> 00:34:55,410
Was it a one-night stand in Yunnan?

545
00:34:55,410 --> 00:34:58,460
What are you blabbering? Don't let your mom and my mom hear you.

546
00:34:58,460 --> 00:34:59,800
Who did you fall for?

547
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:01,010
You know what?

548
00:35:01,010 --> 00:35:05,171
If you weren't pregnant, I would've walloped you. What's this nonsense?

549
00:35:05,171 --> 00:35:07,920
Baby, Mom is so scared.

550
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:10,340
Why is your aunty getting mad?

551
00:35:10,340 --> 00:35:13,200
You're the most annoying.

552
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:17,250
Back to serious matters. Have you found a new job yet?

553
00:35:17,250 --> 00:35:19,756
A new job?

554
00:35:19,756 --> 00:35:23,270
Aunty said you were sick of working at the same hotel in Beijing

555
00:35:23,270 --> 00:35:26,024
for over a decade and want a new job.

556
00:35:26,660 --> 00:35:28,350
How's it going?

557
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:39,670
Slow down.

558
00:35:39,670 --> 00:35:41,370
Mom.

559
00:35:43,090 --> 00:35:44,970
Is there anything I can help you with?

560
00:35:44,970 --> 00:35:47,666
Just wait for food to be served.

561
00:35:55,110 --> 00:35:56,320
Mom.

562
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:58,660
Mom... Mom... What are you doing?

563
00:35:58,660 --> 00:36:00,850
Speak your mind.

564
00:36:02,930 --> 00:36:05,802
How did you know I resigned?

565
00:36:06,970 --> 00:36:09,450
Aunty Sun and Xiao Gang wanted to travel to Beijing,

566
00:36:09,450 --> 00:36:14,280
so she called your hotel in hopes of a discount by mentioning your name.

567
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:18,256
They told her that Manager Xu resigned.

568
00:36:22,380 --> 00:36:25,430
Xu Hongdou, you should know that secrets can't be kept.

569
00:36:25,430 --> 00:36:31,230
Your whole life, every lie you said was exposed.

570
00:36:31,230 --> 00:36:34,320
Since you know about my resignation, why didn't you ask me about it?

571
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:36,220
You seemed like you were having a good time.

572
00:36:36,220 --> 00:36:38,881
Why should I pry? We can discuss it once you're home.

573
00:36:38,881 --> 00:36:40,940
You didn't ask when I got back.

574
00:36:41,340 --> 00:36:43,640
Well, you can tell me now.

575
00:36:43,640 --> 00:36:45,200
It's nothing really.

576
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:48,090
As a child, you said that slower chicks need to start flapping their wings first.

577
00:36:48,090 --> 00:36:50,600
I can't fly anymore. I'm tired.

578
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:53,742
I just want to take a break.

579
00:36:53,742 --> 00:36:55,484
It's fine if you don't want to flap your wings.

580
00:36:55,484 --> 00:36:58,030
It's nice to return to the nest and rest.

581
00:36:58,030 --> 00:37:03,410
Our family can rely on Xu Hongmi, the little cash catcher, to roll in the cash for us.

582
00:37:03,410 --> 00:37:08,040
Just like the swallows under the eaves of your grandma's house.

583
00:37:09,010 --> 00:37:12,840
Mom, I'm not joking.

584
00:37:13,590 --> 00:37:17,030
Okay. Let's talk seriously. What's your plan?

585
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:24,268
Your dad and your sister want you to go to Shanghai.

586
00:37:25,380 --> 00:37:28,616
Actually, I have a friend in HR who reached out to me.

587
00:37:28,616 --> 00:37:30,780
Their hotel is recruiting for staff training.

588
00:37:30,780 --> 00:37:32,410
The job is quite suitable for me.

589
00:37:32,410 --> 00:37:34,734
It's a job with normal working hours.

590
00:37:34,734 --> 00:37:37,380
There's no need to be on 24-hour standby.

591
00:37:37,860 --> 00:37:41,316
That's good. It's fine as long as you like it.

592
00:37:41,316 --> 00:37:42,820
You don't have to worry about me and your dad.

593
00:37:42,820 --> 00:37:44,110
We have some savings.

594
00:37:44,110 --> 00:37:45,450
We don't spend much either.

595
00:37:45,450 --> 00:37:47,410
Besides, there's your sister.

596
00:37:47,410 --> 00:37:49,930
As long as you can feed yourself, we'll be free of worries.

597
00:37:49,930 --> 00:37:52,998
Don't be so stressed.

598
00:37:52,998 --> 00:37:56,630
I don't want to be much worse than my sister.

599
00:37:57,340 --> 00:37:59,988
Why do you always compare yourself with her?

600
00:37:59,988 --> 00:38:01,560
I'm not.

601
00:38:01,560 --> 00:38:05,760
You guys were the ones comparing us ever since childhood.

602
00:38:06,900 --> 00:38:09,510
That's my fault. I shouldn't have done that.

603
00:38:09,510 --> 00:38:12,150
We're in the wrong. I'll apologize to you. I'm sorry.

604
00:38:12,150 --> 00:38:14,110
Mom, you're so quick with admitting you're wrong.

605
00:38:14,110 --> 00:38:15,510
That's too much of a preemptive strike.

606
00:38:15,510 --> 00:38:17,910
I don't even know what to say.

607
00:38:17,910 --> 00:38:19,760
In that case, don't say anything.

608
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,590
Wait for the food to be ready.

609
00:38:21,590 --> 00:38:22,800
Aren't you going to add water to the dumplings?

610
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:25,772
Leave it to me, all right? Just wait for food to be served.

611
00:38:33,860 --> 00:38:36,864
These guys are horrible.

612
00:38:39,030 --> 00:38:40,730
How nice.

613
00:38:46,090 --> 00:38:48,590
All done. It's my turn now.

614
00:38:48,590 --> 00:38:50,170
Okay.

615
00:38:54,110 --> 00:38:56,262
I'll give you a massage.

616
00:38:56,920 --> 00:38:58,220
How is it?

617
00:38:58,220 --> 00:39:00,620
Wow, such strength.

618
00:39:04,160 --> 00:39:07,080
<i>[Xie Zhiyao: How many peaches did you pick? You even made sure everyone has a share. Thank you. Virtual massage for you.]</i>

619
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:09,320
<i>[You must be having a lot of fun back home. You don't even reply to messages.]</i>

620
00:39:22,640 --> 00:39:24,440
What's wrong?

621
00:39:26,130 --> 00:39:27,930
Who is it?

622
00:39:27,930 --> 00:39:30,274
Hongdou is calling me.

623
00:39:30,274 --> 00:39:32,124
Answer it.

624
00:39:37,300 --> 00:39:40,404
Stupid boy.

625
00:39:54,090 --> 00:39:56,310
Hello? Can you hear me?

626
00:39:56,310 --> 00:39:59,860
Hello, are you busy? Why did you take so long to answer the call?

627
00:39:59,860 --> 00:40:03,630
I was with Granny just now. I came upstairs first.

628
00:40:04,860 --> 00:40:07,012
<i>What are you doing?</i>

629
00:40:07,450 --> 00:40:11,200
I am packing up my books. I'm moving to a new house soon.

630
00:40:15,450 --> 00:40:18,230
I didn't have time to reply this afternoon.

631
00:40:18,300 --> 00:40:21,400
My aunty brought my cousin over. It was really bustling.

632
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:23,300
Everyone was making dumplings.

633
00:40:23,300 --> 00:40:27,200
<i>My cousin is several months pregnant. I was accompanying her.</i>

634
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:32,960
No wonder. I wouldn't have been able to pick up your call this afternoon anyway.

635
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:35,290
I was having a meeting about the bookstore in the village.

636
00:40:35,290 --> 00:40:37,260
Any progress?

637
00:40:37,690 --> 00:40:39,870
<i>The team will make a formal visit in a few days.</i>

638
00:40:39,870 --> 00:40:43,310
We were discussing their reception. I'm working with the village.

639
00:40:46,180 --> 00:40:47,840
There's still the homestay.

640
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:50,300
Some guys will come over to survey the place soon.

641
00:40:50,300 --> 00:40:51,756
It's hard to sell the place?

642
00:40:51,756 --> 00:40:54,860
<i>Yeah, it's hard. The potential buyer is offering a very low price.</i>

643
00:40:54,860 --> 00:40:57,820
He just wants a steal. The previous owner is in want of money.

644
00:40:57,820 --> 00:41:01,060
The price has been dropping drastically.

645
00:41:02,180 --> 00:41:04,280
I see.

646
00:41:05,570 --> 00:41:07,230
<i>Let's not talk about that.</i>

647
00:41:07,230 --> 00:41:09,330
They're just troubles weighing on my mind.

648
00:41:20,450 --> 00:41:23,075
<i>- The noodles your mom made...</i>
- How's your throat?

649
00:41:26,700 --> 00:41:29,460
Why didn't you give me a like after you saw it?

650
00:41:29,460 --> 00:41:33,052
